# Web Frontend (VideoScout)

Applies to all work under `web/`. Source of truth: `web/AGENTS.md`, `web/README.md`.

## Next.js

This is **not** the Next.js from training data. Before writing Next.js code, check deprecations and APIs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` for this project's version.

## Tailwind v4 — CSS variables

Use parenthesis syntax. **Never** `-[var(--token)]`.

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| `bg-[var(--surface-muted)]` | `bg-(--surface-muted)` |
| `text-[var(--muted)]` | `text-(--muted)` |
| `border-[var(--border)]` | `border-(--border)` |
| `hover:bg-[var(--surface-muted)]` | `hover:bg-(--surface-muted)` |

Opacity suffix OK: `bg-(--surface-muted)/60`. Tokens: `web/src/app/globals.css`.

## Structure

```
web/src/app/          # routes (App Router)
web/src/components/   # UI by feature
web/src/lib/api/      # typed client + types
```

New API calls: add method in `client.ts`, types in `types.ts`.

## Dev & proof

- Backend must run on **8000** (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` override in `.env.local`)
- Before claiming web work done: `npm run lint` and `npm run build` in `web/`
- Match existing shared components: `page-header`, `tab-bar`, `action-bar`, `stat-pill`, `surface-card`, `btn` classes in `globals.css`

